main event: A white, disc-like object was observed for 30 seconds in Neenah, Illinois by two reliable civilian observers.
interesting points: The object was 60 feet long and disc-shaped., It was reported on September 12, 1952, at 0945 CST., The observers considered reliable were in Netonset, Illinois., The object was seen hovering with no visible wings or propellers., The sighting occurred under clear weather conditions.
